class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4442827\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4442827\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 20, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jne1690876234670.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jne1690876234670.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jne1690876234670.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jky1665702784671\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Function Keys, Shortcuts, and Wildcards\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"jky1665702784671__function_keysshortcutsand_wildcards_13512\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can access menus, retrieve data, and enter and manipulate data using keyboard shortcuts and mouse actions.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jky1665702784671__p_d2555e1_d2556e1_d2557e1\">Functions keys and shortcuts are defined in the keyboard translation table and can be overridden by the definitions in your system's initialization file. Because the keys used to access specific functions can be changed, they are often referred to by logical names in the documentation.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jky1665702784671__topic_d837e1_d838e1_d839e1_d840e1_d841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d769632e56\">\n            \n Gold Key\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jky1665702784671__p_d2561e1_d2562e1_d2563e1\">The Gold key is the logical name of a special Uniface character used for entering structure editor functions, profile characters and subfield separator characters from the keyboard.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jky1665702784671__p_d2564e1_d2565e1_d2566e1\">On Microsoft Windows, the default Gold key is the <span class=\"ph keypress\">+</span> key on the numeric keypad. An alternative mapping is <span class=\"ph keypress\">Ctrl</span>+<span class=\"ph keypress\">Shift</span>+<span class=\"ph keypress\">F1</span>, which is useful on laptops without a numeric keyboard, or on Mac keyboards running Windows. The Gold key is typically used in sequence with other keys. For example, you can use Gold followed by a semi-colon (<code class=\"ph codeph\">;</code>) to enter a subfield character used in Uniface lists.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jky1665702784671__p_d2567e1_d2568e1_d2569e1\">In the Uniface IDE, profile characters and subfield separators are shown in inverse. In documentation, they are represented with an underline. For example, in a Uniface list, the subfield characters are represented as <span class=\"ph gold\">;</span> :</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">apples<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>oranges<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>pears</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jky1665702784671__topic_d842e1_d843e1_d844e1_d845e1_d846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d769632e98\">\n            \n Wildcards and Search Profile Characters\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jky1665702784671__p_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1\">To retrieve or specify only selected data, you can use wildcards and other <dfn class=\"term\">profile characters</dfn>. Valid Uniface profile characters are the Gold key followed by one of: *, ?, =, &gt;, &lt;, !, &amp;, or |.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"jky1665702784671__note_w1247ab1b5b7b5_w1248ab1b5b7_w1249ab1b5_w1250ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Gold profile\n            characters cannot be used in Dynamic or Static Server Page components but you can use\n            the backslash (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\\</code>) instead of Gold for profile characters.</div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Profile Characters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Character </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold * </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Match 0 through n characters of a string,\n\t\t\t\t whether they are printable or not. Cannot be used to match numeric values.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold ? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Match any single character in a string,\n\t\t\t\t whether it is printable or not. Cannot be used for to match numeric values.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold = </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Equals (if used without a qualifier: \"is\n\t\t\t\t null\"). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold &lt; </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Less than </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold &gt; </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Greater than </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold ! </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Logical NOT </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold &amp; </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Logical AND </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__1\"> Gold | <p class=\"p\">Gold ;</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1__entry__2\"> Logical OR <div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When Gold ; is used as a profile character, it is treated as a logical OR, not as a list separator.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jky1665702784671__section_qjz_jq1_4cc\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table frame-all\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_evy_ypg_q3c\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Related learning videos</span></caption><colgroup><col style=\"width:50%\"/><col style=\"width:50%\"/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<th class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__1\">Title</th>\n<th class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" id=\"jky1665702784671__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__2\">link</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__1\">Web Profiling</td>\n<td class=\"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1\" headers=\"jky1665702784671__table_evy_ypg_q3c__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://vimeo.com/showcase/10552636/video/920399583\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Click to watch or listen Web Profiling video\" class=\"image\" id=\"jky1665702784671__image_hg2_wpw_q3c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/My_Video_Button.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/></a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ivf1703097522105.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Gold and Super Key Combinations</a><p>Gold and Super key combinations are defined with ^GOLD_BASE_SET. By default, these key combinations are available in all keyboard translation tables in the USYS library that support a Gold key.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zuz1665702784801.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Profile Characters in Web Applications</a><p>In Web applications, the GOLD character is not recognized, so it is not possible to use the normal Uniface profile characters, such as GOLD * or GOLD ?.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4442827\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4442827\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Function Keys, Shortcuts, and Wildcards Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 20, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Function Keys, Shortcuts, and Wildcards You can access menus, retrieve data, and enter and manipulate data using keyboard shortcuts and mouse actions. Functions keys and shortcuts are defined in the keyboard translation table and can be overridden by the definitions in your system's initialization file. Because the keys used to access specific functions can be changed, they are often referred to by logical names in the documentation. Gold Key The Gold key is the logical name of a special Uniface character used for entering structure editor functions, profile characters and subfield separator characters from the keyboard. On Microsoft Windows, the default Gold key is the + key on the numeric keypad. An alternative mapping is Ctrl + Shift + F1 , which is useful on laptops without a numeric keyboard, or on Mac keyboards running Windows. The Gold key is typically used in sequence with other keys. For example, you can use Gold followed by a semi-colon ( ; ) to enter a subfield character used in Uniface lists. In the Uniface IDE, profile characters and subfield separators are shown in inverse. In documentation, they are represented with an underline. For example, in a Uniface list, the subfield characters are represented as ; : apples ; oranges ; pears Copy Wildcards and Search Profile Characters To retrieve or specify only selected data, you can use wildcards and other profile characters . Valid Uniface profile characters are the Gold key followed by one of: *, ?, =, >, <, !, &, or |. Note: Gold profile characters cannot be used in Dynamic or Static Server Page components but you can use the backslash ( \\ ) instead of Gold for profile characters. Table 1. Profile Characters Character Meaning Gold * Match 0 through n characters of a string, whether they are printable or not. Cannot be used to match numeric values. Gold ? Match any single character in a string, whether it is printable or not. Cannot be used for to match numeric values. Gold = Equals (if used without a qualifier: \"is null\"). Gold < Less than Gold > Greater than Gold ! Logical NOT Gold & Logical AND Gold | Gold ; Logical OR Note: When Gold ; is used as a profile character, it is treated as a logical OR, not as a list separator. Table 2. Related learning videos Title link Web Profiling Related Links Gold and Super Key Combinations Gold and Super key combinations are defined with ^GOLD_BASE_SET. By default, these key combinations are available in all keyboard translation tables in the USYS library that support a Gold key. Profile Characters in Web Applications In Web applications, the GOLD character is not recognized, so it is not possible to use the normal Uniface profile characters, such as GOLD * or GOLD ?. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}